5. strchr()
Meaning
Searches for the first occurrence of a character.

Syntax
strchr(string, character);

Example
char str[] = "Programming";

printf("%s", strchr(str,'g'));

Output

gramming

It returns a pointer to the first 'g'.

6. strstr()

Meaning

Searches for the first occurrence of a substring.

Syntax

strstr(mainString, substring);

Example

char str[] = "Programming";

printf("%s", strstr(str,"gram"));

Output

gramming
